      "writtenOn": "2020-03-02T02:54:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There already is \"drm_atomic\" software deps, and it says \"to synchronize video buffer overlays atomically\". My understanding is \"drm_atomic\" is (almost) arch independent and meaning \"video_overlays\"? If so, I don\u0027t think you need this software deps, instead you can list \"amd64\" and \"drm_atomic\" in your test\u0027s SoftwareDeps.\nIf \"drm_atomic\" and \"video_overlays\" should have different meaning, could you clearly clarify them? (example; \"crossystem\" and \"reboot\" have the same condition at the moment, but they have different concepts so they are defined separately.)",
      "revId": "0f9517e554cd7b8b71e2cf30fb41f6098c24b3d3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
